  "strategy": [
    "Prioritize moving toward blue as soon as blue_seen is detected.",
    "Use commit states for all rotation and forward actions to ensure safe, atomic moves.",
    "After every forward commit, perform a scan (full_rotate) to avoid missing blue and to prevent long straight runs.",
    "After obstacle recovery, always scan before resuming forward movement.",
    "Use recovery states after obstacles to avoid immediate re-entry into forward movement.",
    "Never allow move_forward directly after obstacle_front; always pass through a recovery or scan state.",
    "Avoid oscillations by only allowing one rotation direction per state.",
    "When blue_close is detected, stop immediately to finish the task safely.",
    "If blue is lost during approach, resume exploration via scan and forward commit cycle."
